JD - 1 : 

Key Responsibilities:
- Develop and optimize robotic systems for package handling and logistics automation.
- Implement navigation systems for autonomous vehicles in structured and unstructured environments.
- Work on robotic arms for automated picking, sorting, and placement of packages.
- Implement AI-driven object recognition and package tracking.
- Ensure smooth communication between hardware, software, and logistics control systems.
- Build and refine prototypes to improve performance and reliability.
- Ensure adherence to industry standards and safety regulations for autonomous robotic systems.

Qualifications Required:
- Bachelor/Master degree in Robotics, Mechatronics, Mechanical Engineering, Electrical Engineering, Computer Science, or a related field.
- Minimum 5+ years of experience in designing and implementing autonomous robotic systems for logistics or industrial automation.
- Proficiency in robotic frameworks such as ROS (Robot Operating System).
- Experience with motion planning, SLAM, and real-time navigation.
- Hands-on experience in designing robotic arms with precision pick-and-place capabilities.
- Knowledge of LiDAR, depth cameras, and sensor fusion for navigation and object detection.
- Programming proficiency in Python, C++, and embedded systems programming.
- Familiarity with AI/ML frameworks (TensorFlow, OpenCV, PyTorch) for robotic vision applications.
- Experience with edge computing and IoT-enabled robotics.
- Worked on AGVs or AMRs.
- Experience in warehouse automation, sorting systems, or industrial robotics.
- Familiarity with mechanical design for robotics and real-world deployment challenges.
- Understanding of robotic kinematics, control algorithms, and automation protocols.

